The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 April is 272,903 (31,453.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 April, there were 2,135 new confirmed cases (246.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 April, there were 3,250 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 34% (1,115 fewer cases).
